article.headline: McNeese St. 33, Sam Houston St. 28
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas -- Andre Anderson ran for two touchdowns and McNeese State beat Sam Houston State 33-28 Saturday. The Cowboys (5-4, 4-1 Southland) finished with 439 total offense yards to Sam Houston's 408 yards. Champlain Babin caught a TD pass from Jacob Bower, who finished with 281 passing yards. Diontae Spencer ran for a touchdown, and Josh Lewis kicked two field goals. Anderson finished with 19 carries for 100 yards. Sam Houston's Richard Sincere rushed for two touchdowns, including a 67-yard run in the first minute of the game. Brian Bell threw a 64-yard TD pass to Melvis Pride and finished with 301 passing yards. Two field goals from Miguel Antonio and a safety in the third quarter put points on the board for the Bearkats. The Cowboys are now tied for first place in the conference.
